            <div class="section section-flex" data-id="1197duy17y">
                <div class="section-upper vflex">
                    <h3>Music Interpreter</h3>
                    <div class="flex">
                        <p><img alt="project thumbnail" data-screen="small" width="190px" src="/images/hs-thumbnails/1197duy17y.png" style="float:right;margin:24px 12px 16px 20px;"/>After the introduction of strings, I wanted to create a method that allows the user to write music in Hopscotch with the use of one string instead of having to add blocks for every note or chord in the project. The only change needed for every project is the music string itself; everything else can be copied block for block or with the help of the <a href="/hs-tools/hs-bulder">Project Builder</a> importing <a href="https://awesome-e.github.io/hs-tools/hs-builder/presets/AE_Note-Striker-Engine.hspre">a preset</a>. The best part about working with strings is that custom programs can work with strings much more easily than with Hopscotch block syntax for music. In addition, this method incorporates the my "Keep Sync" chords to eliminate delays between notes in the same chord, as well as user comments to help the user to better understand the string they are working with.</p>
                    </div>
