                    <div class="flex">
                        <p><img alt="project thumbnail" data-screen="small" width="190px" src="/images/hs-thumbnails/zq0f4uiyf.png" style="float:left;margin:24px 20px 16px 12px;"/>As suggested by its name, Smooth Background Generator will generate code for a smooth background based on the preferences of the user. To get started, go ahead and open the project and click start. You will be asked to choose a background style. Choose the colors (it will label each one) and hit "next". Just like that, the code is generated. This project helps new users create cool backgrounds as they can screenshot the code, and it is even useful to more advanced coders like me because it takes away the work of calculating differences between color values to form the background.</p>
